Upstream-PR:     https://github.com/iiab/iiab/pull/4444
Upstream-Status: approved (pending release in the pinned iiab commit)
Applies-to:      roles/proot_services/files/pdsm/usr_local_pdsm/services-available/kolibri
Summary:         Kolibri: seed Studio/KDP "reserved" NetworkLocations at pdsm start (ZeroConf registration does not run under proot)

Mirrors upstream iiab/iiab#4444. Replaces the earlier #4442 "trust system CA"
carry, which did not actually fix Kolibri online import under Android/proot.
Real cause: Kolibri's "reserved" NetworkLocations (Studio/KDP) are created by a
ZeroConf registration event that never fires under proot (netlink blocked), so
they are seeded directly on service start. Applies with -p1 over /opt/iiab/iiab;
the applier fails loudly if the pinned commit's file drifts. Remove once #4444
ships in the pinned iiab commit.

diff --git a/roles/proot_services/files/pdsm/usr_local_pdsm/services-available/kolibri b/roles/proot_services/files/pdsm/usr_local_pdsm/services-available/kolibri
--- a/roles/proot_services/files/pdsm/usr_local_pdsm/services-available/kolibri
+++ b/roles/proot_services/files/pdsm/usr_local_pdsm/services-available/kolibri
@@ -26,6 +26,20 @@
   # Ensure nginx is up as a requirement
   require_service "nginx"
 
+  # Seed Studio & KDP "reserved" NetworkLocations if absent.
+  # Normally created via the ZeroConf registration event, which does not
+  # run under proot (netlink is blocked). Seed directly.
+  reserved_count=$(sqlite3 "${KOLIBRI_HOME%/}/networklocation.sqlite3" \
+    "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM discovery_networklocation WHERE location_type='reserved';" \
+    2>/dev/null || echo 0)
+  if [ "${reserved_count:-0}" -eq 0 ]; then
+    echo "[pdsm:$SERVICE_NAME] seeding reserved network locations (Studio/KDP)"
+    "$KOLIBRI_BIN" manage shell -c \
+      "from kolibri.core.discovery.tasks import _refresh_reserved_locations; _refresh_reserved_locations()" \
+      >/dev/null 2>&1 || \
+      echo "[pdsm:$SERVICE_NAME] WARNING: reserved-location seeding failed (continuing)" >&2
+  fi
+
   "$KOLIBRI_BIN" start
 
   # Small wait loop so 'start' only returns when it's actually alive
